    "summary": "My career started with a Bachelor degree in Mechanical Engineering, including international experience due to internships  in Australia and in Nicaragua. My first fulltime job was with IHC where I started as Trainee and worked my way up to assistant Superintendent Technical Services at IHC. My interest in Maritime Engineering resulted in other interesting jobs with Boskalis and Bosch Rexroth/Allseas. \n\nOn August 2016 my girlfriend and I decided to travel around the world for one year. The main reason was to get a better understanding of the world, different cultures, and languages. \nWe returned back to the Netherlands (Den Haag) with many new experiences and ambitions. \n\nMy personal qualities which are:\n- Solving problems\n- Planning\n- Teamwork\n- Coordination\n- Analytical\n- Practical minded\n\nMy goal is to enforce an engineering department or technical project team. It's important to me that the professional relationship between my colleagues/manager is always improving. With professional relationship I mean: \n- respect each other \n- understand the strength and weaknesses of each other\n- aim for the best team performance\n\nMy special interests are a broad range of fields, for example:\n- Innovative Project Engineering\n- Commissioning systems \n- Asset Management \n- Renewable Energy \n- Rail infrastructure and transportation\n\nMy special qualities are international experience and languages. Countries where I gained work experience are: Australia, Nicaragua, India, Dubai, Qatar, Scotland, England, Germany.\nLanguages I speak fluently: Dutch, English, Spanish (moderate), German (moderate).\n",
